<br>
But from what I have read the skald gets progressively worse as you level to 50.  Opponents get better protection with their skills, abilities and spell crafted armor, and we do not increase in ability to compensate.  At high levels a skald is a shadow of his former self, basically a very light tank at best, not able to fight alot unless in support, and primarily useful just for the run song.<br>
<br>
So my question is this, to the experienced skalds out there.<br>
<br>
Assuming there are no changes from mythic which will improve the above, (and I think that is a good assumption), is there a spec and realm abilities that you would recommend that will somewhat mitigate this, optimizing our abilities at high level and preventing us from being nothing more than a speed-bot? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=panthian>Panthian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/14/03 1:34:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mitigating being a gimp at high level</span><hr size=1> Here is my spec/RA outlook if there are no changes<br>
<br>
46 Battlesongs (I do a lot of PVE raiding so wanted the DA)<br>
47 Axe<br>
5 Parry<br>
<br>
RA list in my priority level<br>
<br>
Long wind<br>
FA1<br>
FA2<br>
IP<br>
Purge<br>
Toughness1<br>
Aug Acuity1<br>
<br>
That should keep ya busy for a while :P<br>
 <p>Panth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=strivar>Strivar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/14/03 1:41:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> What about the aug dex 1 &amp; 2 and the Mastery of Pain line  (to help us with our melee ability by increasing the criticals)?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=panthian>Panthian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/14/03 4:10:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't consider those until after the list I provided was attained.<br>
<br>
Aug dex is worthless (IMO) really because our parry/evade is so poor so I would rather pick up 6% hp increase (toughness2) and 6 cha (aug acuity1) before 12 dex and 5% extra chance to crit.  I feel that hp is greater then all but others might disagree .. no biggie.<br>
<br>
